    A representation of the model object 'Table Row'.

    A concrete TableRow is an object instance mapped on a database table row.

    The object may be logically deleted (isDeleted()), meaning that it is physically deleted (as is or to be) in the database, but not in the application:

    • UpSynching a table with a row removed, will not remove the corresponding object in the application but will set it as IsDeleted.
    • DownSynching an object set as IsDeleted will delete it from the database table.

    Following information about the execution of the synchronization is returned

    • getModificationLastSynchUp() : modification on the object done by the last up synch
    • getModificationNextSynchDown() : modification on the table to be done by the next down synch

    The following features are supported:

    • Table
    • Current Key
    • Deleted
    • Index Key
    • Last Synch Down Key
    • Last Synch Down Deleted
    • Modification Last Synch Up
    • Modification Next Synch Down
